<TITLE> Bangladesh in Group D of Under-19 World Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh have been placed in Group D along with group's top-seeded England, Bermuda and Ireland in the ICC Under-19 World Cup to be played in Malaysia from February 17 to March 2. Holders Pakistan will play against hosts Malaysia in one of four opening day matches, said an ICC media release from Kuala Lumpur Wednesday. Pakistan, India, Australia and England have been top-seeded in each of four groups as a total of 16 nations, split in four groups, will play first round group matches. Bangladesh, who finished fifth in the 2006 in Sri Lanka and emerged the Plate Champions in 2004 in Dhaka, are in comparatively easy group as top two teams from each group will qualify for the Super League and two bottom teams for the plate championship. Group A includes Pakistan, Malaysia, New Zealand and Zimbabwe, Group B consists of India, the West Indies, South Africa and Papua New Guinea. Australia, Sri Lanka, Nepal, and Namibia are in Group C. Bangladesh will start their campaign playing against Bermuda on February 18 and take on Ireland on February 20. Bangladesh will play their group's last match against England on February 22. The final is scheduled for March 2 in Kuala Lumpur. 
